Patrick T. Anderson's cover letter:

I've been programming professionally in C and C++ since 1995.

I have strong knowledge of Windows internals and have used the Win32 API, MFC and some ATL and COM to write services with GUIs, tray icons, alerts.

I am familiar with entire registry both as a user (through regedit), and programmatically through the Win32 API.

I have used threaded programming off and on for most of my career, understanding both theory and implementation details.

I have a solid understanding of (X)HTML, and have used it along with Javascript for user interaction.

I am slightly familiar with ODBC, Java and Perl, Python, PHP.

I've been using and programming on GNU/Linux off and on for 10 years.
